videos.description: Elijah Macon pulls the Mountaineers to within four after he drives the lane and gets the layup, plus the foul.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Macon gets the and-1 to fall

videos.description: Bears guard Al Freeman drains the shot from beyond the arc to give Baylor a 23-20 lead.
videos.headline: Baylor's Freeman knocks down 3 to take the lead

videos.description: Jake Lindsey finds Johnathan Motley for the slam to keep Baylor within striking distance.
videos.headline: Motley throws down the dunk for Baylor in the 2nd half

videos.description: Bears forward Johnathan Motley spins around a West Virginia defender on his way to the dunk, and the foul.
videos.headline: Baylor's Motley hammers home the monster jam

videos.description: Bears guard Jake Lindsey comes through in a big way with the late layup, plus the foul.
videos.headline: Lindsey puts Baylor up 10 late with the and-1 lay-in

videos.description: Baylor's Johnathan Motley talks with sideline reporter Kris Budden following the Bears 71-62 win over number ten West Virginia.
videos.headline: Johnathan Motley post game interview
